This recipe worked fine as basic template for a shepherd's pie, but if prepared exactly as written, a little bland and lacking in substance. As others have noted, it's pretty bland unless some seasoning tweaks are made. I also found the idea that this would serve 6 people, assuming we're talking about average sized adult humans, absurd. I more than doubled the ingredients in the recipe (making close somewhere between a 2.5X and a triple batch), and ended up with 8 modest (French onion soup bowl) portions. Had I divided these to get the 15 or so portions suggested by the recipe, the dish would not have sufficed as a main meal. I think it would be helpful if Epi changed the servings to 4, or even 2-4.

