Rating: 4
I tried the original recipe agree that the recipe can be on the bland side. To make it sublime, you need to reduce the broth by a 1/3 or 1/2. I double the broth, add some cognac (or try red wine), simmer with carrots, garlic, onions, and rosemary (strain and discard afterwards) and reduce by half. This makes for a beefier and more well- rounded flavor -- tasting like it was long simmered rather than the quick 10 min on stovetop. This makes it rustically delicious, with a beautiful developed and robust flavor. I make and assemble this in individual ramekins, one day ahead, so I can pop it in the oven right after work for the family dinner (Next time I will try with turkey meat to reduce the fat content.)

