Rating: 3
When I read the list of ingredients, I worried that this would be another bland casserole recipe. So I changed the recipe based on what I had on hand, and thought it was pretty good. But I made a few changes... I like a moist casserole. I'll add more liquid next time, or maybe even layer the potatoes & meat/onion mix so the potatoes can get some o that great gravy. I hate carrots, so I skipped those & used Brussel sprouts instead. I think this would be great with green beans, or different root veggies. I recommend, if you use ground lamb, you use 2-3 lbs because by the time you brown & drain fat from the lamb there's not a lot of meat left. I seasoned the meat with garlic, a bit of Lawry's seasoned salt, & McCormick's Worcester pepper. Also added a couple dashes of Cholula hot sauce (not too hot, but great flavor). If I'd had it on hand, I would have added Cheddar cheese. This recipe has a lot of potential for American diners, with a little tweaking!

