Just made this tonight and it was great, a keeper...I followed some of the suggestions offered by others. I added half a zuch and half a summer squash chopped, a cup of chopped criminis and 3 cloves of garlic. I also used some worchestershire and more rosemary than called for. Salt and pepper of course and everything else as called out in the recipe. I was able to purchase some lamb raised by a local Amish farmer, so no hormones or drugs...all natural with only a few hymns to sing it to sleep in the evening. Fabulous flavor and not too strong. For the spud topping I use about 2/3 yukon golds and 1/3 parsnips. 3 roasted garlic cloves, 2/3 cup sharp white cheddar an 1/2 cup parm cheese. Butter as specified and heavy cream for the milk. These I'll make by themselves for holidays in the future! For those that say it is a bland dish, since everything is cooked ahead, you have plenty of opportunity to "adjust the seasonings" so there's really no excuse. Make it! You'll love it

